{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17413176","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17413176"},"attributes":{"position":10,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-28T07:59:21+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-28T07:59:21+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1261100"}},"session":{"data":{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1261100"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16594"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17539407","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17539407"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T17:41:19+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T17:41:19+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16594"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1261100","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionSessions/1261100"},"attributes":{"startedAt":"2025-09-28T07:52:04+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-28T10:28:52+09:30","sessionType":"qbank","questionStatus":"all","difficulty":[],"timeLimit":null,"questionCount":62,"questionsAnswered":61,"marksTotal":61,"marksAttainable":61,"marksAttempted":61,"finishedAt":"2025-09-28T09:15:31+09:30","resultsAvailable":true,"score":0.2,"questionsCorrect":12,"marksCorrect":12},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"pack":{"data":{"type":"packs","id":"5"}},"exam":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questions","id":"16594","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16594"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.02,0.12,0.74,0.11,0.01]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9285"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"90211"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9285","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9285"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16594"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"74456"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"10"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"225"},{"type":"tags","id":"2982"},{"type":"tags","id":"3166"},{"type":"tags","id":"4886"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"21993"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25039"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"90211","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/90211"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 23-year-old woman presents to the Emergency Department accompanied by her parent with a two-week history of unusual behaviour. She has no significant medical history and takes no regular medications. Her parent reports she was previously a high-achieving university student but has recently stopped attending classes and spends most of her time in her room talking to herself.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, she appears dishevelled with poor eye contact. Her pulse rate is 82/min, blood pressure 118/72 mmHg, respiratory rate 14/min, SpO2 99% on room air, and temperature 36.7\u00b0C. When asked about her mood, she responds: \u0027The purple mathematics dances through doorknobs because clouds make triangles sing underwater. Yesterday tastes like wooden rainbows when silence walks upstairs.\u0027 Her speech has normal rhythm and grammatically correct structure. She demonstrates thought blocking, concrete thinking, and social withdrawal. She follows basic commands and is not aggressive. A urine drug screen is negative.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes this patient\u0027s speech pattern?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Circumstantiality","Flight of ideas","Word salad","Tangentiality","Pressured speech"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThis patient demonstrates \u003Cstrong\u003Eword salad\u003C/strong\u003E, characterized by grammatically intact sentences containing completely unrelated or nonsensical content. While the sentence structure remains correct, the content consists of random words strung together without logical connection or meaning. This is a severe form of formal thought disorder commonly seen in schizophrenia spectrum disorders.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFlight of ideas\u003C/strong\u003E differs in that there are discernible, albeit loose, connections between concepts. The speaker rapidly moves between related ideas in a way that, while difficult to follow, maintains some logical thread. For example: \u0027I\u0027m feeling happy... the sun is happy... the sun is yellow... bananas are yellow... I\u0027m hungry.\u0027\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECircumstantiality\u003C/strong\u003E involves providing excessive, unnecessary detail before reaching the point, but ultimately arrives at the intended destination. The speech maintains logical connections throughout, even if the path is indirect.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETangentiality\u003C/strong\u003E occurs when responses to questions start on track but veer off into unrelated topics, never returning to answer the original question. Unlike word salad, individual thoughts remain coherent and logically connected.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPressured speech\u003C/strong\u003E refers to the rate and rhythm of speech rather than its content. It is characterized by rapid, urgent speech that is difficult to interrupt, but the content maintains logical connections between ideas.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe key distinguishing feature of word salad is the complete absence of logical connections between concepts while maintaining grammatical structure. This differs from other thought disorders where some degree of logical association, however loose, is preserved.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Word salad is characterized by grammatically intact sentences containing unrelated or nonsensical content","Word salad differs from flight of ideas where associations between concepts are tangentially related","Formal thought disorder must be distinguished from pressured speech and circumstantiality which maintain logical connections"],"references":["Sadock BJ, Sadock VA, Ruiz P. Kaplan and Sadock\u0027s comprehensive textbook of psychiatry. lippincott Williams \u0026 wilkins; 2017 May 11.","Mota NB, Copelli M, Ribeiro S. Quantifying word salad: The structural randomness of verbal reports predicts negative symptoms and Schizophrenia diagnosis 6 months later. arXiv preprint arXiv:1610.08566. 2016 Oct 26."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"74456"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16594"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"74456","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/74456"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-03-12T19:56:53+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-03-12T19:56:53+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9285"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"90211"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"10","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/10"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udfad","name":"Psychiatry","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:46+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"64","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/64"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Diagnosis","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position